<br>
EQ simply will not sunset for years after EQII is released. Simply - I don't think the return on investment for POP and Ykesha development is going to go into the black anytime soon, but the reality is that two EQs are better than one, and they will both be healthy revenue streams - I'm sure many people will play both, all the time. Software doesn't just shut off.<br>
<br>
Empere <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kamdarentilzha>Kamdar Entilzha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1098<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(2/6/03 11:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1064.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/Kam_small2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ok next step</span><hr size=1> EQ2, not to mention Star Wars: Galaxies, which is coming out this spring, have been on my mind for quite some time now.  <br>
<br>
I am actually excited about both games, but certainly don't look forward to losing the friendships and camaraderie we all now share.  I have even been wondering if we could carry the guild over to include other games (can you say Exodus Alliance anyone?). <br>
<br>
SWG will be EQ set in the Star Wars universe and folks will be able to be anything from a mercenary to a Jedi.  It's made by many of the folks that developed EQ.  I sure would like to see SOE offer subscribers who want to play both, a deal on the monthly charges.  I mean, how many games can people afford?  And now SOE seems to be competing with itself!<br>
<br>
From what I hear EQ2 will be different in some other ways as well.  I believe they intend to go back to the original 3 continents and they will be much bigger.  Traveling across the lands will cover huge expanses and bank items will not transfer.  So people may have to set up some kind of convoys to safely carry their belongings from place to place, if they intend on changing their home base.  Horse will be more prevalent and homes to keep all your stuff in may also be available.  Though it scares me to think how much they will cost!<br>
<br>
If these things indeed are still planned, it should prove to be a bit of a different game and I think I may welcome some of the changes.  Some of you may think I'm crazy, but I think the ease that we can all travel to the farthest reaches of Norrath and Luclin is a mixed blessing.  The world may have many more places to visit, but it just doesn't seem that big anymore.  I remember my first boat ride and how excited I was to see a new land (even if it was Erudian!)  The first time I made it to Rivervale from Qeynos under my own power seemed like quite an accomplishment to me (there were a couple of failed attempts, but I had a great desire to see the land of the Halflings!).  I then moved onto Freeport and that city eventually became my new home.  <br>
<br>
Now, I think travel is just too easy.  I would wager that there are players in their 40's and beyond who do not even know how to get from Qeynos to Freeport without some kind of a teleport.  I know, who needs to waste all that time traveling, right?  There's leveling to be doin!   As I say, to me its a mixed blessing, the world used to seem much more immerse to me.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's probably one of the reasons I will welcome EQ2.  I also can't wait to see the new graphics in operation.  I recently checked out the beta of Asheron's Call 2 and you could see reflections in the water.  It was pretty sweet.  I hope EQ2 will be able to accomplish that, and more.<br>
<br>
But for now, I think we need to get the most out of our time together.  Let's have as much fun as we can.  Maybe a bunch of us will move on at some point... maybe we'll move on together...  Maybe we'll form The Exodus Fellowship Part Deux with Hiking as our leader!  Who knows what the future will bring.  But, if we have a desire to, we will find a way to stick together.<br>
<br>
Kamdar<br>
